parameters: There is one crystal placed in each map.
You can recover here, so please make use of it for dungeon conquest.

I'm glad we found a good spot. Can I really use the tent? Let's all go
in together after all!

I express a little bit of exasperation, telling you not to push
yourself too hard.

Hmm... You might be okay if you push yourself, but I think it's really
cramped.

Also, it's dangerous for everyone to be inside the tent in case
something happens, so someone needs to keep watch outside.

I'll take turns keeping watch with Light, so I'll ask Lira to be
cautious of the food inside the tent.

Leave it to me! ...Huh? Are you saying I'm not needed in a roundabout
way?!
I wonder if \n[1] trusts Lira and said that to me.
Hehe, thank you both so much.
I said it at the beginning, but it's still fun, this kind of thing...
Everyone has more and more things they need to do, huh?

There are many opportunities to go outside for the sake of the
village. Eventually, I'm sure there will be more time spent elsewhere.
I'm not worried, but I wonder how \n[1] feels?

Lira's mother's cooking is exquisite, so she will probably return to
the village regularly.

Of course, I also like everyone, including Lira and \n[1], so there's
nothing to worry about.
Is that so... If that's the case... I'm happy.

Ah, so rest assured and good night. Let's all do our best together
from tomorrow.
Yeah... everyone together... all together... *stomach growls*

Honestly, Lira has been a worrier since the old days. I think it just
means she cares a lot.

Shall I carry it to the tent? Come to think of it, \n[1] always took
care of Lira, didn't he?
Let's do our best from tomorrow so that Lira can feel at ease soon.
I don't really do things like camping, so it's a bit refreshing.

Before coming to the village, Margaret lived in a big city, and even
after coming here, she mostly stays holed up in the shop, so she might
not have many opportunities to go outside.
In that sense, Margaret is the most elegant in the village, isn't she?
Even though I was in a big city before I can remember--

When it comes to being elegant, it's definitely Azami-san... a mature
woman.
In my heart, I feel like Margaret is the opposite of me.

Now.. I'm sure that even if I think of something rude, in the blink of
an eye, I'll become like Azami-san... probably.
Does Light have something to say too? I'm all ears.

Huh!? ...Ah, no, it's not like that. I was just a little lost in
thought.

It's already late today, so let's go to bed early and prepare for
tomorrow. Shall \n[1] and I take turns keeping watch?

Thank you. I'll do my best to be as helpful as possible in other
matters, so please continue to rely on me from tomorrow onwards.
Hey, hey- why won't \n[1] sleep with me?

He said I'm a lady, so he has to treat me with care. *averting her
eyes*
Eh?! What do you mean by that?!

If you're going to say that much, then I'll wait until \n[1] is
emotionally ready!

At first, I wondered how this group would turn out, but surprisingly,
they're getting along quite well.
We've never done anything with just the three of us before.

Let's keep up the pace and quickly explore, and then let's swiftly
lift Light's curse!

Honestly, I never thought Miiru would be this useful. When I first
picked her up, she was really naive...

Hey! That's in the past, as long as I'm doing well now, there's no
problem!

That's right, \n[1]. From my perspective, Miiru has changed a lot.
Probably more than anyone else in our group.
As expected of Light! You understand, don't you!
Well, there are some things to discuss, but let's just rest for today.
That's right, both of you, good night!

Even though we went through the trouble of setting up the tent, Light
can be a bit strange at times, suggesting that we should watch the
night sky together.
This sky is so beautiful, it's not really strange, is it?

If we're talking about being strange, I honestly think \n[1] is much
more so.
Haha... Please don't make such a dissatisfied face.
I'm grateful, surely if \n[1] wasn't here, I wouldn't be who I am now.

That must be a story from when we first met, so there's no need to
worry. It was all just self- satisfaction.
...Haha... Sorry for saying something strange all of a sudden.

You've been through a lot lately, right? That's why I wanted to tell
you again.
He sighed, thinking about how that aspect has changed.

Well, I guess I'll just have to accept that it's partly \n[1]'s
responsibility that I turned out this way.

At this rate, we might end up talking until morning. We have
exploration to do from tomorrow, so please rest first. Let's take
turns keeping watch at a suitable time.
I'll take your words at face value and rest first.

Even though it was said to be deep in the forest, I was able to sleep
peacefully that day. It must have been because Light was by my side.
